<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06248051 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06248051 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  Sonoma County sheriff's deputies are searching for a man who allegedly nearlybit his wife's lip off during a fight at their Santa Rosa home. Sheriff'sofficials said the incident was reported about 11:30 p.m. Monday when deputieswere summoned to an apartment at 2358 Corby Ave. Annie McCarter-Jordan, 32,told deputies that her husband, Robert Jordan, 40, had forced his way into herhome and assaulted her. She told investigators that during the assault, herhusband bit her lip and tore a portion from her face.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  HUSBAND IS SOUGHT IN SEVERE LIP-BITING  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Bay Area in Brief  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910904  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  September  </MONTH><PG.COL>  3B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  92  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday, September 4, 199100248051,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>